article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- — Cameron Huefner had 14 points in Sam Houston's 65-54 victory against UTEP on Saturday night. Huefner was 4 of 9 shooting, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line for the Bearkats (17-11, 10-3 Conference USA). Davon Barnes scored 12 points, going 4 of 8 (2 for 4 from 3-point range). Lamar Wilkerson had 10 points and was 4 of 10 shooting (0 for 5 from 3-point range). Otis Frazier III led the Miners (13-15, 4-9) in scoring, finishing with 14 points and two steals. Zid Powell added 10 points, six rebounds and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
